cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the challenges and considerations for designing accessible visualizations, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY) as well as information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and graphics (cs.GR). The focus on participatory methods and disability studies also suggests a potential fit with the social and information sciences (cs.SI).
